=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  MOVE01 -> calc work field
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: build path, external tiny source-deck loading, fixed H/F/I/C/O
  source parsing, two decoded I-spec fields, a tiny parsed calc subset
  (currently MOVE and REVR), and two selectable O-spec output definitions.
- Placeholder today: the subset is still tiny; there is no general RPG
  parser, no general C-spec execution beyond that small calc subset, no general
  O-spec formatting, and no arbitrary user-supplied RPG program execution.

Current runtime-produced output:
RECORD 01A
RECORD 02B
RECORD 03C

